name: Ibuprofen
description: A nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID) used to relieve pain, fever, and inflammation.

name: Acetaminophen
description: Commonly used for pain and fever relief.

name: Amoxicillin
description: A penicillin antibiotic used to treat a variety of bacterial infections.

name: Ciprofloxacin
description: A fluoroquinolone antibiotic used for infections of the skin, bone, and urinary tract.

name: Acyclovir
description: An antiviral drug used to treat herpes virus infections.

name: Oseltamivir
description: An antiviral used to treat and prevent influenza (flu).

name: Fluconazole
description: Used to treat various fungal and yeast infections.

name: Terbinafine
description: An antifungal medication used for treating athlete's foot and other fungal infections.

name: Loratadine
description: Relieves allergy symptoms like sneezing, itching, and runny nose.

name: Cetirizine Syrup
description: A liquid antihistamine for treating seasonal and perennial allergies.

name: Sertraline
description: A common selective serotonin reuptake inhibitor (SSRI) used for depression and anxiety.

name: Fluoxetine
description: Used to treat depression, obsessive-compulsive disorder (OCD), and panic attacks.

name: Alprazolam
description: A benzodiazepine used for anxiety and panic disorders.

name: Diazepam
description: Used to treat anxiety disorders, alcohol withdrawal symptoms, and muscle spasms.

name: Lisinopril
description: An ACE inhibitor used to treat high blood pressure.

name: Amlodipine
description: A calcium channel blocker for high blood pressure and chest pain.

name: Metformin
description: Used to improve blood sugar control in people with type 2 diabetes.

name: Glipizide
description: Used to lower blood sugar in people with type 2 diabetes.

name: Atorvastatin
description: Reduces 'bad' cholesterol and triglycerides.

name: Simvastatin
description: A statin drug used to treat high cholesterol.

name: Naproxen
description: A nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug (NSAID) for pain and inflammation.

name: Prednisone
description: A corticosteroid used to reduce inflammation in the body.

name: Tums
description: Calcium carbonate tablets for heartburn and indigestion.

name: Maalox
description: Liquid antacid for the relief of heartburn, acid indigestion, and gas.

name: Gabapentin
description: Used to treat seizures and nerve pain.

name: Levetiracetam
description: An anticonvulsant used to treat various types of seizures.

name: Methotrexate
description: Used to treat certain cancers and autoimmune diseases.

name: Doxorubicin (IV)
description: A chemotherapy drug administered intravenously to treat various cancers.

name: Levothyroxine
description: Treats an underactive thyroid gland (hypothyroidism).

name: Estrogen Patch
description: A transdermal patch for hormone replacement therapy.

name: Albuterol
description: A fast-acting bronchodilator for asthma attacks.

name: Albuterol Inhalation Solution
description: Used in a nebulizer to relax airway muscles.

name: Warfarin
description: An anticoagulant (blood thinner) used to prevent blood clots.

name: Rivaroxaban
description: An anticoagulant for deep vein thrombosis and pulmonary embolism.
